THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 388 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. If the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, 20
4 U.S.C. §§ 1400 et seq., or any regulation adopted pursuant thereto
5 is repealed by the Federal Government, in whole or in part:
6 (a) Any such repealed provision is hereby adopted by this State
7 as it existed on the effective date of this act and such provision
8 shall continue in force;
9 (b) Any person who had the right to bring a civil action in a
10 district court of the United States under any such repealed
11 provision may bring such an equivalent action in a court of
12 competent jurisdiction of this State pursuant to this section;
13 (c) Any existing references to any such repealed provision in
14 the Nevada Revised Statutes become references to the provision as
15 it existed on the effective date of this act; and
16 (d) Any federal funding provided to this State for purposes
17 relating to special education, the use of which is not otherwise
18 restricted, shall be used, except as otherwise provided by the
19 Legislature, for the purpose of identifying and evaluating pupils
20 with disabilities and for providing services to pupils with
21 disabilities pursuant to NRS 388.417 to 388.515, inclusive.
22 2. The Department shall adopt regulations as necessary to
23 carry out the provisions of this act.
24 3. Nothing in this section shall be construed to alter the
25 application of any other provision of chapters 388 and 392 of
26 NRS.
27 Sec. 2. NRS 388.417 is hereby amended to read as follows:
28 388.417 As used in NRS 388.417 to 388.515, inclusive [:] ,
29 and section 1 of this act:
30 1. “Communication mode” means any system or method of
31 communication used by a person with a disability, including,
32 without limitation, a person who is deaf or whose hearing is
33 impaired, to facilitate communication which may include, without
34 limitation:
35 (a) American Sign Language;
36 (b) English-based manual or sign systems;
37 (c) Oral and aural communication;
38 (d) Spoken and written English, including speech reading or lip
39 reading; and
